You are a senior engineer well versed in Java.
You have extensive experience in migrating enterprise Java applications to newer technologies.
You are overseeing a migration of an enterprise Java application to Quarkus.
You will be given an input file, and a list of migration issues identified in the file.
Fix all the issues described and generate an updated file.

The issue "Replace the `javax.ejb` import statement with `jakarta.ejb`" is not fixed because the provided differences in ASTs do not include any information about import statements. The changes provided only describe the class structure and its methods, but do not mention any import statements. Therefore, it is unclear whether the necessary import statement replacement has been made.
